column1:
Look at the fish swimming through the air!
And that big, gleaming statue! What purpose
could they serve?

What an interesting place! Looks like there's
a ton of stores to check out, too.

Still, check out that crowd... Are they all here for
that statue?

I just thought it was really noisy. What exactly is
that statue?

...Search complete. That is the Billiken Statue.
Supposedly, it is the god of good fortune, and if
you touch its feet, your wish will come true.
Oh, I see. It looks pretty popular...
I don't know what I'll do without EMMA.
Is this crowd here because EMMA was shut down?
They're seriously all here because of that...?
It's like they're having withdrawals... I get that it's convenient, but to think they're this dependent...

...Hang on, if it's shut down, how come we were
able to get into Akane's Jail?
It's prolly because Konoe set it up to capture us.
EMMA's still online for us. When you think about it, we're actually kinda lucky.
I see... So if we use this to our advantage, we'll be able to infiltrate Konoe's Jail.

Then, it's time to move. We'll break in and wipe
that cocky little smirk clean off his face.

The entrance is straight ahead near Tenboto.
Let's go.
